name: Os quindins de yayá
comments: In the film Donald Duck and José Carioca travel to Bahia where they see a woman (Aurora Miranda) carrying a basket full of quindins that she is trying to sell and singing "Os Quindins de Yayá". A large group of men soon gather around her and join in the song. On the official film soundtrack (Shellack box), the song was sung by Nestor Amaral .

comments: This rendition became identified with the Maidan Revolution (aka The Revolution of Dignity) which took place in Kyiv after months of large-scale protests (known as Euromaidan) caused by Ukrainian President Yanukovych's refusal to sign a political association and free trade agreement with the European Union. In February 2014, clashes between the protestors and the police resulted in 130 victims (incl. 18 police officers). This song honours those who died there defending democracy and freedom of the Ukrainian people.
